name: Qwen Code
description: An open-source AI coding agent that runs in the terminal, optimized for Qwen3-Coder model. Provides CLI-based autonomous coding assistance with repo-aware capabilities and multi-file project support. Latest nightly release v0.7.0-nightly.20260111 demonstrates active development.
community_quotes: Open-source AI agent that lives in the terminal
Optimized for Qwen3-Coder model with strong performance

name: SeaVerse AI Native Platform
description: World's first AI Native Platform called 'All in AI Native,' focused on forward-looking revolution in AI creation and development workflows. Launched as a comprehensive AI-native development environment.

name: Spec Coding by Capacity
description: A spec-driven AI development platform that enforces 'spec-first' approach to building full-stack web applications. Instead of chaotic 'vibe coding,' users define specifications first with an AI planning assistant, then generate production-ready code. Reached #1 Product of the Day on Product Hunt with 311 upvotes.
community_quotes: Vibe coding with a planning assistant to build with clarity
Ask first, build later - a spec-first approach to AI-assisted development
Reached #1 Product of the Day on Product Hunt
Helps eliminate technical debt in AI app development through spec-driven coding

name: IQuest-Coder-V1
description: An open-source coding AI model family (7B-40B parameters) that uses innovative Code-Flow Training to learn from repository evolution patterns and commit histories. Achieves state-of-the-art performance on SWE-Bench Verified (76.2%), LiveCodeBench v6 (81.1%), and BigCodeBench (49.9%), matching or beating models 10-20x its size.
community_quotes: Matches or beats Claude Sonnet 4.5 and GPT models with only 40 billion parameters - 10x to 20x smaller
Uses innovative Code-Flow Training that learns from commit histories and repository evolution instead of static code snapshots
First coding AI release of 2026 that came from an unexpected source - a Chinese quantitative hedge fund
The Thinking variant with reasoning-driven RL is specifically optimized for complex algorithmic problem solving
Fully open source with weights, training code, and evaluation scripts all available under modified MIT license
